In `map_module_to_address`, there is `request.module` (which is `"pacifica.cli"`), while the provided results are `ModuleProvider`s with `Address`es (`Address(//:root#pacifica-cli), Address(pacifica_db/pacifica/__init__.py:../pacifica-db-src-sources)`).

So IIUC, I need to make both the 1st and 3rd party `providers_for_module` functions either return `AddressAndDistancePairs` or `AddressAndModulePairs` and then do the resolution in `map_module_to_address`.
Is that correct?

Another option is to (somehow) get the mapping from [the root `BUILD` file](https://github.com/TalAmuyal/pants-repro/blob/namespace_collision_example/BUILD) which has the exact mapping we want:
```python
{
    "module_mapping": {
        provider.addr.generated_name: [request.module],
    }
}
```
I've pushed a third commit that serves as an example for that one.

